    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trademarked name for a nontoxic method of insect eradication that uses a microprocessor-based system that targets susceptibility of insects to elevated temperatures while keeping moisture content and dimensions of organic materials stable during heating. In conservation, used for eradication of woodworm and moths in art and antiques.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
